research_municipality_step.notes: North Bergen Township operates under the Walsh Act form of New Jersey municipal government, where five commissioners are elected at-large, and they select one of their members to serve as mayor. The listed officials and their roles are based on the official township website and a news article from May 2023 regarding the swearing-in of the current board.
